SA artisanal cheesery hopes virus will boost Slow Food Cheddar-making was put on hold when coronavirus struck an artisanal cheesery on the outskirts of Clarens, a town tucked into the foothills of the Maluti mountains of central South Africa. Hard cheeses requiring months of ripening were no longer viable, and the small business battled to stay afloat as sales plummeted. Cheesemaker Marietjie Crowther only managed to produce small amounts of her signature smoked mozzarella and chilli-infused "string cheese". Worldwide coronavirus cases cross 14.3 million, death toll at 600,497 More than 14.3 million people have been reported to be infected by the novel coronavirus globally and 600,497â€‹ have died from COVID-19, according to a Reuters tally. Infections have been reported in more than 210 countries and territories since the first cases were identified in China in December 2019. -REUTERS